<H2>today.pl -- Highlight Today's Date in Unix Cal Output</H2>
<HR SIZE=3 NOSHADE WIDTH="100%">

<A HREF="perl/today.pl"><B>today.pl</B></A> is a simple way to highlight
today's data in unix cal program output. Note that more modern cal
programs, such as the one from the GNU project and a recent BSD cal do by
default highlight today's date in the calendar output.

This program is more a curiousity of how I did it before cal did the
highlighting.  

<H3>Usage</H3>
<P>The command line is: 
<TT><FONT COLOR="#000080">today.pl</FONT> </TT>
There are no commandline options for today.pl.

<UL>
    <LI>ncal output will also work. /usr/bin/ncal -h -b'; # -h is turn of highlighting of today
    <LI>ncal by default also highlights the day by default.  
</UL>

<P>As an example, the command 
<TT><FONT COLOR="#000080">today.pl</FONT></TT>
might produce output like:

<IMG SRC="/personal-tech/gif/today_example.png" ALT="today.pl example output">


